The Chronicle Mthabisi Tshuma, Showbiz Correspondent Pumula North Hall was a hive of activity on Tuesday as an array of young artistes from around Bulawayo converged to showcase their talent as they celebrated Africa Day. <img class="wp-image-548527 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Pumula.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Pumula.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Pumula-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Pumula junction dance crew The event that was dubbed My Heritage Show ran under the theme “Embracing my African Heritage through arts and culture”. It was a colourful event that was organised by the Home of Arts Entertainment in partnership with Yellow World, Hustle Gang and New City Style. <img class="wp-image-548529 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/New-city.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/New-city.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/New-city-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> New City Style models Diverse artistes – Indosakusa the Morning Star Juniors, Pumula Arts and Craft, Msheli Wentombi, The Maskandi guy, Sammy C, Mandy the S.B, Reliance, Ginger Stone, DrloveNj, Vanessa Tsuro the model, Infinity Art, Pumula junction dance crew and New City Style took turns to entertain the attendees. <img class="wp-image-548530 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Pummula-arts.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Pummula-arts.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Pummula-arts-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Pumula Arts and Craft In attendance were Pumula MP Hon Sichelesile Mahlangu, deputy mayor Clr Mlandu Ncube, Ward 17 Councillor Skhululekile Dube, representatives from the Ministry of Youth, Sport, Arts and Recreation, ZRP, residents and youths from around Bulawayo. <img class="wp-image-548533 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Mtsheli.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Mtsheli.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Mtsheli-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Msheli Wentombi performing where he is joined in dance by Bulawayo deputy mayor Clr Mlandu Ncube, Pumula MP Hon Sichelesile Mahlangu and representatives from the Ministry of Youth Speaking after the event, Home of Arts Entertainment director, Happy Mpofu said the event lived up to its billing as local artistes were given the platform to showcase their art. <img class="wp-image-548534 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/The-Infinity-Art.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/The-Infinity-Art.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/The-Infinity-Art-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The Infinity Art “The My Heritage Show, a youth-led initiative whose aim was to embrace the African Heritage through arts was held to promote the different talents that young people have. Also, it was meant to encourage other youngsters who’re yet to discover their purpose and talent,” said Mpofu. – @mthabisi_mthire